    <h1 style="text-align: center;">Bachelor of Computer Applications (BCA)</h1>
   
    <section>
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            The Bachelor of Computer Applications (BCA) is a three-year undergraduate program in computer science and information technology. It equips students with the essential skills and knowledge to pursue careers in software development, IT, and computer science fields. The course is designed for individuals who are passionate about technology and aspire to build a career in the IT industry.
        </p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Course Highlights</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Duration: 3 years (6 semesters)</li>
            <li>Eligibility: 10+2 or equivalent with a minimum percentage (varies by institution)</li>
            <li>Focus Areas: Programming, software development, database management, and networking</li>
            <li>Career Opportunities: Software Developer, System Analyst, Web Developer, Network Administrator</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Core Subjects</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Programming Languages (C, C++, Java, Python)</li>
            <li>Web Development (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)</li>
            <li>Database Management Systems (MySQL, Oracle)</li>
            <li>Operating Systems</li>
            <li>Software Engineering</li>
            <li>Data Structures and Algorithms</li>
            <li>Computer Networks</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Skills Developed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Problem-solving and analytical thinking</li>
            <li>Proficiency in coding and software development</li>
            <li>Understanding of IT infrastructure and networking</li>
            <li>Knowledge of database systems and management</li>
            <li>Team collaboration and project management</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Career Prospects</h2>
        <p>
            BCA graduates have a wide range of career options in both private and government sectors. Popular job roles include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Software Developer</li>
            <li>Web Developer</li>
            <li>Database Administrator</li>
            <li>System Analyst</li>
            <li>Network Administrator</li>
            <li>IT Consultant</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Graduates can also pursue higher education such as MCA (Master of Computer Applications) or other IT-related postgraduate programs.</p>
    </section>
